**Abstract:**
A detailed outline/appendix to EXCOR-3, dated April-May (year unspecified). The document provides a structured summary of arguments against Ex Corde Ecclesiae's epistemological presuppositions, organized into nine sections: the chiasm, preliminary considerations, impartiality and medieval reason, criticism of medieval notion of reason, speculative and practical reason, the medieval synthesis, knowledge as judgment, the incompatibility of Aristotle's theoretical and practical reason, and practical knowledge in Aristotle. Concludes with section on faith as practical knowledge, arguing medievals mistakenly assimilated faith to theoretical knowledge.

**AI Recommendation:** Detailed outline summarizing the Ex Corde critique; useful reference for the structure of the author's arguments.

